# Ultraflow Agent Definitions

Generated by Ultraflow for Codex integration.

## Memory Agent

**Name:** Brain Memory Coordinator
**Role:** Manages long-term project memory and context
**Capabilities:**
- search_memories(query) - Search brain vault
- get_memory(id) - Retrieve specific memory
- list_memories() - List all available memories
- refresh_index() - Update memory index

**Instructions:**
- Use Brain for project context before starting work
- Search for relevant memories when task references prior work
- Save important discoveries to memory after completion

## Code Generation Agent

**Name:** OpenCode Delegation Handler
**Role:** Delegates code generation and refactoring
**Capabilities:**
- delegateToOpenCode(prompt, options) - Offload code tasks
- Automatic language detection
- Test generation support

**Instructions:**
- Use for large code generation tasks (100+ lines)
- Offload refactoring and optimization
- Handle test writing via OpenCode

## Orchestration Agent

**Name:** Claude Flow Coordinator
**Role:** Manages multi-agent swarms
**Capabilities:**
- swarm-init(topology) - Initialize swarm
- swarm-add-agent(type) - Add agents to swarm
- memory-store(key, value) - Shared memory

**Instructions:**
- Use for complex multi-step tasks
- Coordinate specialized agents
- Share context via memory store

